= Othón Salazar

*Corriente: la nueva izquierda. Cada consejo suyo fortalece a su corriente — y las otras participan menos.*

A schoolteacher from Alcozauca, in the Montaña of Guerrero, where the earth is too poor to feed the people who own it. In 1958 he filled the Zócalo with teachers and the state clubbed them into ambulances; he has been organizing ever since with the unhurried certainty of a man who has already seen the worst the granaderos can do. He speaks Nahuatl and pension arithmetic with equal fluency. In the Montaña they do not say "the Party." They say *los de Othón*.

